CLIENT SPOTLIGHT 🫶🏼⚡️

I am SO unbelievably proud of how far Sharna has come in the last 12 weeks both mentally and physically 🥲 Yes her results are amazing but this isn’t just a 12 week before and after. Sharna was completely lost with her nutrition but has learnt so much along the way and now knows the importance of fuelling her body with the right foods! Together we worked on not only changing what she ate but also her daily habits and mindset ⚡️

Sharna absolutely put in the work each week - she was bright and early with her check ins and prepped her meals as soon as I gave her the weeks meal plan. She would often put in requests for foods she felt like and we ALWAYS made it work! 

The process doesn’t have to be boring, the proof is in the bloody pudding - look at her!! She absolutely smashed it!! 

Losing a total of 5.6kgs and 28cm all around! I am BEYOND proud 🫶🏼 

If you’re ready to transform click the link in my bio for more details 🤭

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

CREAMY ITALIAN PASTA SALAD 

Ok peepz here it is!! love love love a pasta salad, especially this Italian one - it has all the flavour! 🤭 high in protein even on its own or serve up as a said salad with some nyummy meat (chicken for me hehe) 

✍️ recipe
Pasta:
375g pasta - I used @vettapasta protein pasta 
1 green capsicum
1 punnet of cherry tomatoes (250g)
1/2 Lebanese cucumber 
1x 220g tub cherry bocconcini balls @lacasadelformaggio 
1x jar black sliced olives @alwaysfreshau 
*optional - fresh herbs to top! I used parsley 😊

Sauce:
210g greek yoghurt I used @chobaniau 
10g white or red wine vinegar - I used white 
10g extra virgin olive oil - (usually use way more but I just needed to cut back the cals for my meals😂 use 1/4 cup if you wish)
Italian herbs 
Tsp minced garlic 
S&P

👩‍🍳 Method 
•Cook pasta as packet directions 
•In a small bowl combine greek yoghurt and vinegar - mix to combine 
•add in olive oil, S&P, and Italian herbs. Set aside
•Prep veggies & drain olives and bocconcini 
•Assemble pasta salad with pasta at the bottom, veg on top and then pour sauce over 
•mix to combine and top with fresh parsley 
•pop in the fridge before serving 😇 

Macros - serves 5
Per serve 
Cals 471 P30g F17.4g C46.4g

#pastasalad #proteinpasta #dinner #mealprep

HONEY PB OAT BARS 

Perf little snack bar that’s super easy to make! Obsessed with the honey PB atm 🤤 

✍️ recipe
210g rolled oats @uncletobys 
150g PB - I used the HONEY flavoured @mayversfood PB
150g honey 
5ml vanilla extract 
Pinch of salt 
50g protein powder - I used @atpscience collagen unflavoured protein 
10g choccy chips - I used sugar free @noshufoods 

👩‍🍳 method
• whisk together PB, honey, protein, salt, vanilla
• stir in oats until combined 
• press into lined 8x8 tin 
• top with choccy chips 
• whack in the freezer or fridge to harden up a bit, then cut into 10 slices 😊 I store mine in the fridge 

Macros for the recipe above 
10 serves // per serve 
Cals 235 P10.7g F8.7g C28.3g 

#honey #mayvers #peanutbutter #energybar #protein #proteinbar #atpscience

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

HIGHER PROTEIN RASPBERRY WHITE CHOC BANANA BREAD 

Approved by the household taste testers - Steve & coop 🤣

✍️ recipe 
120g frozen raspberries 
400g banana - 3 large ripe nanis or 4 medium/big 
80g honey
50g raspberry jam - I used @natvialiving sugar free 
50g coconut oil (melted) 
200g protein flour @vettapasta - can sub for normal flour
50g protein powder - I used @atpscience Noway collagen vanilla
100g @whittakersnz blondie chocolate (tastes like caramilk) 
3g baking powder 
Pinch of salt

👩‍🍳 method
•preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius 
•mix all ingredients together minus the raspberries and the jam until combined
•fold through raspberries and choccy
•pour into a lined nani dish
•top with blobs of raspberry jam and swirl with a knife or spoon or chopstick 
•bake for 50-60 mins or until toothpick comes out clean 
•let cool before slicing 

Warm it up when serving and top with some greek yoghurt and raspberries or butter 🤤 this ones flava is seriously amaze 

Per slice - 10 slices 255 cals P10.5g F9 C32g

#bananabread #proteinsnacks #baking #recipeoftheweek #atpscience

CHICKY WRAPS 

Ok but I will never get over this folded wrap trend, it’s been years and it’s still my favourite way to make my chicken wraps nek level 😂 perfectly balanced with all the goods ✌🏻 

✍️ recipe
• 150g chicken breast 
• @mingleseasoning seasoning taco 
• lettuce
• cheese slice - I used @begacheese higher protein less fat
• cherry tomatoes 
• avocado 
• mingle bbq sauce 
• 2x @helgas.bakehouse low carb wraps

👩‍🍳 
Coat chicken & cook for 20 mins in the air fryer
Shred with 2 forks
Cut a line into the centre of the wrap
Assemble wrap in whatever order your heart desires 
fold it up and whack it in a sandwich press 🥲 

Macros for both wraps
Cals 579 P56.6g F20g C39.3g 

#lunch #wraps #protein

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

DOUBLE CHOC • PB // PROTEIN BITES 

Been a little sick but I’m back! Okeh I love making little treatys to keep in the fridge but they never last long when Steve’s home 🙃 these are srsly so smooth and fudgy, if you haven’t tried them yet this is your sign 🙊 

✍️ RECIPE 
DRY 
* 1 1/2 cups quick oats @uncletobys 
* 2 scoops Protein Powder - I used choccy flavoured NOWAY from @fbosupps 
* 1/2 cup cocoa powder @woolworths_au 

WET
* 3/4 cup smooth peanut butter I used @mayversfood 
* 1/4 cup SF maple syrup @queenfinefoods 
* 1/2 cup milk - I used unsweetened oat @vitasoy_aus_nz 
* 1/2 cup SF dark chocolate chips - I used @noshufoods 

TOP 
* 1 tsp coconut oil @naturalrawc 
* 2/3 cup SF dark chocolate chips @noshu
* drizzle of PB 

*To try the NOWAY protein powder that I absolutely love in all my baking, use the code DEE at @fbosupps for money off 🫶🏼

👩‍🍳 METHOD 
1. Mix together the oats, chocolate protein powder and cocoa powder
2. In a small bowl, melt the chocolate in the microwave then add in the smooth peanut butter, maple syrup and milk 
3. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and mix 
4. Line a baking dish. Spread and press the mixture in the dish with the back of a spoon
5. In a small bowl melt the coconut oil and chocolate - roughly 90 seconds. Stop every 30 seconds and mix 
6. Pour melted choccy over the base
7. Freeze for at least 2 hours - or refrigerate. I left mine over night in the freezer 🥰
8. When she’s ready cut into slices 
9. Store in a lil lunch box in the refrigerator for up to 1 week (they won’t last that long) xoxo 

*I cut mine into 20 bits and the macros per bite are 
181 cals P8.4g F10.5g C9.7g

#proteinbar #mayvers #peanutbutter #proteinsnacks

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

COCO LEMON OATS 🍋 

If you have a spare lemon hanging around, make these oats for your next breakfast holy shmoly 🥵🥵 Im currently in a phase of sweet breakfasts atm and I am loving all the flavour combos 🙊

👩‍🍳 Recipe 
Base 
1/2 cup oats
1/2 cup milk (or water) - I used unsweetened almond @vitasoy_aus_nz 
tsp chia seeds
1 scoop of protein - I used @atpscience NOWAY vanilla
Drizzle of maple syrup @queenfinefoods 
Tbsp yoghurt - I used @yoproau 
Lemon juice 
Lemon rind 

Topping 
1/3 cup yoghurt - I used yopro
20g white choccy - I used @cadburyaust baking choc 

👩‍🍳 method 
• combine all oats ingredients in a small bowl or container and leave to set in the fridge while you do the yoghurt layer 
• melt choccy in microwave (30 second intervals) and mix in with the yoghurt
• layer the yoghurt mix on top of the oats and refrigerate overnight to set (or for 4 hours min)
• sprinkle over some shredded coconut and top with some fresh lemon slices 

Enjoyyyyyyy 

*use the code DEE at @fbosupps for money off your supps🫶🏼 this is where I get my FAV protein - atp science NOWAY 

Macros for the above 🫶🏼
Cals 484 
P33.2g F15.5g C48.3g 

#protein #oats #proats #lemon

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

CREAMY CHICKEN PASTA BAKE 

Had some of my favs over for dinner and I made them this pasta bake - she was a hit 🙊 I find it hard to make meals look nice but the flavour slaps

✍️ RECIPE 
• 375g pasta - I used @vettapasta protein pasta 
• 80g sun dried tomato strips in oil (drained and cut up) I used @alwaysfreshau 
• fresh herbs to top - I used parsley 
• 100g spinach 
• 600g chicken breast 

SAUCE
• 30g unsalted butter
• 10g minced garlic
• 60ml chicken stock reduced sodium I used @woolworths_au 
• 50g flour - I used protein flour @vettapasta 
• 500ml milk (warmed up) I used oat milk but full cream is good too 
• 250ml LIGHT thickened cream
• 375ml chicken stock reduced sodium
• 200g light shredded cheese
• 70g finely grated parmesan 
• parsley to taste
• garlic powder to taste 
• onion powder to taste 
• S&P 

👩‍🍳 METHOD
* preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius 
* Cook pasta as packet direction 
* Cut chicken into thinner slices and season with S&P. Cook for 3/4 mins each side then remove to cool. 
* Cut into bite size pieces 

SAUCE
* melt butter and garlic over medium heat. Add in 60ml of chicken stock and stir
* Add in flour and pour in milk slowly. Whisk to combine
* Once combined, add in the rest of the chicken stock and the cream. Keep whisking 
* Stir for 4/5 mins until the sauce has thickened 
* Add in seasonings, parmesan and most of the cheese (save some for top) 

BAKE
* once sauce is thick add in spinach, sundried tomatoes, pasta and chicken
* Pour into a baking dish and top with the rest of the cheese 
* bake for 25 mins 
* Top with fresh parsley 🥰😋 

#protein #dinner #pasta #pastabake

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

SUMMER SALAD OF YOUR DREAMS 
With sun dried tomatoes, feta and cous cous

I literally make this salad so much in the warmer weather and with the sun shiningggggg I was really craving it, especially after getting all my fresh produce from @angelostreetmarket 🥲 bloody unreal!!!! 

✍️ what you need
• 1 cup of cous cous
• tbsp vegetable stock
• can of chick peas
• sundried tomatoes in oil
• red onion
• cucumber
• capsicum 
• rocket
• feta
• minced garlic 
• S&P

👩‍🍳 method
• combine cous cous, chickpeas, minced garlic and seasoning in a bowl. Cover with boiling water for 5 minutes
• prep veg
• fluff out cous cous mixture with a fork and assemble salad 😎 

* serve with a source of protein - I do crumbed chicken 

#salad #summersalad

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

CHICKEN CAESAR PASTA SALAD // meal prep 

The most simple, tasty & balanced meal prep - you don’t need to over complicate it 🥲 you can definitely make your own caesar sauce however I picked up the tastiest ready made one from @angelostreetmarket along with the other ingredients 🥰💫 idk why but I’m obsessed with pasta salads lately - anyone else?? 😂

✍️ RECIPE - per 1 meal 
* 50g pasta uncooked
* 120g chicken breast 
* panko crumbs 
* lettuce 
* shaved parmesan 
* 30ml caesar salad dressing - I used @finefoodwa 
* croutons - I used rosemary & sea salt croutons by @riccisbikkies 

👩‍🍳 METHOD
* cook pasta as packet directions, then let cool 
* cut chicken into bite size pieces and crumb. Air fry for 20 minutes then let cool
* wash and cut lettuce
* pop everything into a bowl and mix 
* sprinkle parmesan on top and walaaaaa
ENJOYYYY 💫

#caesar #pastasalad #lunch #mealprep

CINNY NANI BREAD - higher protein 🫶🏼

Okay I am actually OBSESSED with this one - I’ve made many nani breads but this one just wow. You will not regret it 🥲 

⚡️ What you’ll need:
WET 3 large ripe bananas mashed  1/3 cup melted coconut oil
1/2 cup granulated sweetener of choice - I used stevia but any will work - light brown, coconut or white  3 large eggs 1/2 cup greek yogurt  1 teaspoon vanilla extract

DRY 1 cup flour - I used oat flour (blended my own oats) 1 cup all purpose flour - I used protein flour 1/2 cup protein powder - I used Cinnamon churro by muscle nation @musclenation @musclenationfood 
3 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon cinnamon 1/4 teaspoon salt
1/2 cup chocolate chips optional

⚡️if you wanna save some $$ on your protein or MN supps use code “FUELWITHDEE” at musclenation’s check out⚡️

⚡️Method
- Preheat the oven to 160 degrees Celsius
- Spray and line a 9×5 loaf pan and set aside
- Mash the 3 bananas and add to a large bowl 
- Add in all the other wet ingredients and whisk until combined 
- Add in the dry ingredients
- Mix until smooth
- Fold in the chocolate chips 
- Pour into loaf pan and top with extra choccy chips 
- Bake for 55-65 minutes 
- Let cool for 25 minutes before cutting
- Enjoy right away with some butter, nut butter or mix together some yoghurt and cinnamon and lather it on 🤤 

#bananabread #cinnamon #musclenationfood

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️

CREAMY PASTA 🍝  high in protein 

This is one of the household favourites 🤩 Love creating pasta sauces in the blender - actual game changer! 
You can add roast veggies, spinach, literally whatever!! This combo is just bloody amazing though if you love sun dried tomatoes

⚡️What you’ll need 
• 375g protein pasta - I use @vettapasta 
• 700g chicken breast - raw weight seasoned in garlic & herb @mingleseasoning 
• parmesan cheese 
• fresh basil 
• 5g minced garlic 
S&P
* herbs of choice - parsley & basil are great 

SAUCE 
• 390g (1 3/4 cup) milk - I used oat milk @vitasoy_aus_nz 
• 60ml (1/4 cup) light thickened cream
• 60ml (1/4 cup) light sour cream 
• 20g tomato paste 
• fresh basil
• jar of sundried tomato (I use the Woolies brand in oil and drain and shake off excess oil) @woolworths_au 

⚡️How to make it 
• cook pasta as per packet instruction
• *if using* cut chicken into bite size pieces, season with garlic and herb & s&p 
• in a pan, put in 2 tbsp of the sun dried tomato oil and the minced garlic then add in chicken 
• while that’s all happening, drain the sun dried tomatoes and shake off excess oil 
• blend together sauce ingredients and add s&p to taste 
• save 1/4 cup of pasta water before draining the pasta and add little bits at a time to the sauce mix to get you’re desired consistency 
• combine pasta, chicken and sauce in a large bowl or back in the pot to warm it up and stir to combine 
• top with the parmesan cheese and more fresh basil 
* makes 5 servings, kinda gotta eye ball the servings

5 SERVES // PER SERVE (approx) with chicken 
Cals 534 • P52.9g F13.6g C47.2g

#proteinpasta #pasta #pastalover

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

MEDITERRANEAN CHICKEN NOURISH BOWL 🫶🏼

Back with a bowl, my fav way to eat the rainbow 🌈 🤩 
Try switching up your rice to quinoa - it’s a complete protein (contains all nine essential amino acids) high in fibre & minerals and low FODMAP for ppl with sensitive guts ✨

⚡️ What you’ll need 
• 170g chicken breast 
• 150g sweet potato - seasoned with garlic & herb @mingleseasoning 
• chickpeas 
• lettuce
• 50g uncooked quinoa 
• tomato
• cucumber
• red onion 
• wedge of lemon

Marinade 
1/4 lemon juice freshly squeezed 
Fresh parsley 
5ml extra virgin olive oil
Pinch of salt 
1g of each - or to taste 
Paprika 
Thyme 
Garlic powder 
Coriander * if you wish 
Dill 

Sauce
• yoghurt - I used @yoproau 
• splash of vinegar 
• lemon juice
• dill
• S&P 

🌈 How to 
• combine the lemon juice, olive oil, cumin, garlic powder, paprika, salt, thyme, and coriander to create a marinade 
• Cut chicken breast in half to make thinner slices and marinate for 15 minutes
• cut sweet patatas into cubes and season 
• Pop chicken in the air fryer or roast in the oven - for 20 minutes @ 180 degrees along with the sweet potato 
• cook quinoa 
• prep veg 
• mix sauce 
• assemble bowl ✨ 

#buddhabowl #nourish #eattherainbow

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

CHOC PB CHIA PUD

I literally love meal prepping for the convenience - come home from the gym early in the morning and a yum breaky is waiting for me 🥹 

☀️ What you’ll need for 3 chia puds 
(Divide by 3 to get the measurements for 1 if you only want 1)
⚡️ 120g chia seeds
⚡️ 420ml milk of choice 
⚡️ splash of maple syrup or honey for the sweetness 

For the choc splash - makes 3 serves 
⚡️ 150g frozen banana (2 medium) 
⚡️ 240g greek yoghurt I use @mundellafoods 
⚡️ 3 scoops of choc flavoured protein
⚡️ 45g drippy natural peanut butter - I use @mayversfood 
* might need a splash of milk or water esp if you’re not using a high speed blender!! 

☀️ How to
⚡️ mix together chia pud ingredients and pop in the fridge to set (maybe an hour or so) 
⚡️ blend choc splash ingredients together 
⚡️ pour choc mix on top of chia mix and top with walnuts 😊 
⚡️ pop back into the fridge until you’re ready to eat, then top with more fresh banana or fruit if you wish xoxo 

#chiapudding #chocolate #peanutbutter

⬇️

I was pretty shocked at how many DM’s I had asking for the recipe from my story yesterday, so I decided to make another lil bowl today. It was the perfect lil snacky snack in this heat 🥵 

Also, I always thought getting nice thicc smoothies/bowls meant you’d need lots of ice but this had no ice 🥹 why did no one tell me sooner?? And a good blender!! 

What you’ll need 
🌸 2.5 cups of frozen fruit (I used half strawb half raspberry) 
🌸 up to 1/4 cup milk or water - I used oat milk 
* use little bits at a time - it’s better to start with less and keep adding to get your desired consistency 
🌸 scoop of vanilla protein - * totally optional 

Literally whack it all in and blitz 
* you’ll need to stop it to mix everything around and then blitz again x a few times 
* use a good high speed blender tho because this never worked in my previous blender 

THEN top with whatever your heart desires 😋 I did granola, PB, shredded coconut and 1/2 a banana xoxo

🌸 lil bowls are @kmartaus 

#smoothiebowl #smoothie

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

She’s not the prettiest, I will keep practising my pretzel skills 🥨 but she sure tastes gewddddd 

What you’ll need - per 1 pretzel
⚡️85g self raising flour
⚡️65g yoghurt 
⚡️ egg wash 
⚡️ Pinch of salt if you wish 

How to
⚡️Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius 
⚡️ Combine flour, salt & yoghurt in a bowl
⚡️ Using your hands mix until a dough forms - trust the process, keep mixing !! 
⚡️Once a dough has formed, let it sit for 10 mins covered 
⚡️roll out into a long sausage then turn it into a pretzel shape
⚡️ top with egg wash and pop in oven at 180 degrees Celsius for 15-18 minutes - until golden brown 
⚡️ top with whatever your heart desires!! 

* I mixed together 1 TBSP cinnamon crunch protein powder with water to create a glaze. Then topped with cinnamon sugar 😊 

#protein #pretzel

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

Slow cooked chicken is a must in our household, at least once a week I make a batch of some kind of slow cooked chicken to have ready for meals or just some chicken to snack on - depending on what flavour we make burritos, wraps, fajitas, nachos, buddha bowls, salads, sliders, sandwiches, rolls, pasta, soup, pizzas, fried rice - literally anything!! 

It takes 1 min to prep then 6-8 hours on the slow cooker and she’s done for the week! I can get about 6 meals out of 3 large breasts (1.2kg) so if you need something super easy and healthy but most importantly YUM, you will want to make this 🤤 

What you’ll need for this mexi chicken
⚡️ 3 large chicken breasts
⚡️ 1x can of corn (drained and rinsed) 
⚡️ 1x can of beans (drained and rinsed) 
⚡️ jar of salsa
⚡️ 30g taco seasoning - with no nasties @mingleseasoning 
⚡️ lime 
⚡️S&P to taste 

How to
⚡️ place chicken beasts in the slow cooker pot
⚡️ dump on the beans, corns, salsa and seasoning
⚡️ turn to low and let cook for 6-8 hours (if you’re short on time cook on high for 4) 
⚡️ take chicken breasts out and use 2 forks to shred 
⚡️ put it all back into the slow cooker pot and mix together
⚡️ squeeze in fresh lime juice and top with coriander if you wish!! 

#slowcooker #mex #mexicanfood

SANTA BROWNIES 🎅🏼🌲🫶🏼

Yay Christmas is hereeeeee!! This brownie is absolutely to die for - even without the Christmas toppings. Yes you can absolutely enjoy these things, all in moderation 😊🫶🏼 you don’t have to eat only raw treats xoxo

Also the egg splash on my shorts gives me the ick too 🙃 

What you’ll need 
🎅🏼 90g flour- I used protein flour 
🎅🏼 30g cacao powder 
🎅🏼 20g chocolate protein powder - I use ATP science NOWAY 
(dc: DEE for $$ off @ elitesupps) 

🎅🏼 150g sweetener - I use stevia 
🎅🏼 2 eggs

🎅🏼 175g dark chocolate - I used sugar free 
🎅🏼 200g unsalted butter 

🎅🏼 Christmas toppings, I used @kitkatanz Santa’s 😊

How to 
🌲 preheat oven to 160 degrees Celsius 
🌲 line 9x9 tray with baking paper and set aside 
🌲 in a small bowl, melt together butter and chocolate - 45 second intervals. Mix together then set aside to cool to room temp 
🌲 in another bowl, crack eggs and mix in sweetener - whisk until kinda foamy
🌲 once it’s cooled down a bit, pour chocolate mixture into egg mixture. Fold together to combine 
🌲 fold in dry ingredients - flour, protein powder & cacao 
🌲 once combined, pour into baking tray and pop in oven for 25 minutes
🌲 take out of oven and add your Christmas decorations - I used little candy canes and chocolate Santa’s 
🌲 cut up and enjoyyyyyyy 

#christmasrecipes #christmasbrownies #christmas

RECIPE BELOW ⬇️ 

RASPBERRY SWIRL OAT BARS for @elitesuppsaustralia 💜

use my dc code: DEE to save $$ off your fav supps 🫶🏼 
I used the macro mike vanilla buttercream protein in this one

I’m talking cranberries, white chocolate, raspberries, vanilla buttercream protein, oats mmmmm mmmm 🤤 I love my oat slices but this one just hits the bloody spot 🥹 
SO hard not to eat the whole tray 

What you’ll need 
DRY
🌲 1.5 cups oats 
🌲 2x scoops of protein - I used macro Mike vanilla buttercream from @elitesuppsaustralia 

WET
🌲 3/4 cup drippy natural peanut butter 
🌲 1/4 cup SF maple syrup
🌲 1/2 cup water/milk - I used oat milk! (splash bit more if it’s dry, just depends on what protein you use) 
🌲 1/2 cup dried cranberries 

TOPPING
🌲100g white chocolate 
🌲 tsp coconut oil 
🌲 frozen raspberries (defrosted) 

How to 
🌟 line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside
🌟in a bowl, combine oats and protein powder 
🌟add in PB, maple syrup and milk of choice then mix to combine 
🌟 fold in cranberries 
🌟 press mixture into prepared baking tray 
🌟 melt chocolate and coconut oil in the microwave in 30 second increments 
🌟 pour mixture on top of oats and use the back of a spoon or a spatula to spread 
🌟 blob some raspberries across the choccy and use something to swirl it through, I used a cocktail stirrer with coops head on it 😂😂 
🌟 freeze for a couple of hours and then take out to cut
🌟Once you’ve cut it up store it in the fridge xoxo

#christmas #christmasrecipes #raspberries #elitesupps

RECIPE BELOW ⭐️ 

I had someone in my DM’s asking for the recipe of the cookies we posted on my story yesterday SO here it is! 

Miss Independent making Chrissy cookies 💛 we were supposed to bake together but she did all the fun stuff and I did the cleaning up 🤣 life of on an aunty xx

RECIPE 
🌲 1 cup plain flour 
🌲 1/4 cup maple syrup 
🌲 1/3 cup melted butter - unsalted 
🌲 pinch of salt
🌲 vanilla extract - she free poured so I’m not sure 🤣 

TOPPING
⭐️ melted chocolate - we used caramilk @cadburyaust 
⭐️ Christmas sprinkles 

HOW TO
🧑🏻‍🎄 preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius 
🧑🏻‍🎄 mix everything together in a bowl until a dough forms
🧑🏻‍🎄 roll it out and press your cookie cutter shapes into it
🧑🏻‍🎄 roll out the left over dough and repeat until all is used 
🧑🏻‍🎄 bake for approx 10 mins 
🧑🏻‍🎄 lay on a cooling rack and wait 5 mins for them to cool
🧑🏻‍🎄 melt choccy and dip half the cookie in 
🧑🏻‍🎄 chuck on some sprinkles and walaaa

This literally the easiest and yummiest snacks to make! Ermagerd these ones really do slap 😛

What you’ll need
🍌 banana
🥜 natural drippy peanut butter 
🍫 chocolate - I used sugar free choc chips 
* top with crushed almonds 

How to
Cut your nani into slices
Freeze for a couple of mins then wipe PB on top
Make little sandwiches then freeze for 10-15 mins
Cover in melted chocolate and top with crushed almonds straight away
Keep in the freezer until you’re ready to eat 🫶🏼 

Brands:
I used @mayversfood PB & @noshufoods chocolate

PESTO PASTA SALAD 

What you’ll need 🫶🏼
* 1x pack spiral protein pasta 
* 1x pesto sauce - I used sundried tomato but you can use any flavour 
* 1 cucumber
* Half a red onion
* 2 roma tomatoes 
* 60g spinach/rocket mix 

How to ✌🏻
* cook pasta as packet directions
* Meanwhile, prep all the veg (you can use whatever veg you like!) 
* Assemble the pasta salad in a large bowl with pasta at the bottom then veg and the pesto sauce at the top

The brands I use are 
@vettapasta 
@leggosau
